{
  "local_port": 36874,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to check your PF balance?",
  "response": "Checking your Provident Fund (PF) balance is essential to ensure your retirement savings are accurately updated. In India, the Employees' Provident Fund Organisation (EPFO) provides multiple convenient methods to check your PF balance. Below are the detailed procedures for each method:\n\n### **1. Online via the EPFO Member Portal**\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- **Unified Account Number (UAN):** Ensure your UAN is activated and linked to your Aadhaar, PAN, and bank account.\n- **Password:** You should have set a password for your UAN.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Visit the EPFO Member Portal:**\n   - Open your web browser and go to [https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/](https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/).\n\n2. **Login to Your Account:**\n   - Enter your **UAN** and **password**.\n   - Click on the **\"Sign In\"** button.\n   - If logging in for the first time, you might need to reset your password using your registered mobile number.\n\n3. **Navigate to the PF Balance Section:**\n   - Once logged in, look for the **\"View\"** dropdown under the **\"Dashboard\"** section.\n   - Select **\"View EPF Passbook\"** or **\"EPF Balance\"**.\n\n4. **View Your PF Balance:**\n   - Your current PF balance, along with historical contributions, will be displayed.\n   - You can also download or print your PF statement for future reference.\n\n### **2. Through the mYPF Mobile App**\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- **Smartphone** with internet access.\n- **mYPF App:** Available on both Android and iOS platforms.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Download and Install the App:**\n   - Search for **\"mYPF\"** in the Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n   - Download and install the app on your device.\n\n2. **Register/Login:**\n   - Open the app and log in using your **UAN** and password.\n   - If you're a new user, you might need to register using your UAN details.\n\n3. **Access Your PF Balance:**\n   - Once logged in, navigate to the **\"Claim\"** section.\n   - Your current PF balance will be displayed on the dashboard.\n\n### **3. Via SMS**\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- **Active UAN:** Must be linked with your Aadhaar number.\n- **Registered Mobile Number:** The mobile number should be linked to your UAN.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Compose an SMS:**\n   - Type **\"EPFHO UAN ENG\"** for English or **\"EPFHO UAN HIN\"** for Hindi.\n\n2. **Send the SMS:**\n   - Send the SMS to **7738299899**.\n\n3. **Receive Your PF Balance:**\n   - Within a few minutes, you will receive an SMS containing your latest EPF balance.\n\n### **4. Using the UMANG App**\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- **Smartphone** with internet access.\n- **UMANG App:** Available on both Android and iOS platforms.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Download and Install the App:**\n   - Search for **\"UMANG\"** in the Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n   - Download and install the app on your device.\n\n2. **Register/Login:**\n   - Open the app and navigate to the **\"EPFO\"** services.\n   - Log in using your **UAN** and password.\n\n3. **Check Your PF Balance:**\n   - Select the option to view your **EPF balance**.\n   - Your current balance along with contribution details will be displayed.\n\n### **5. Through Your Employer\u2019s HR Department**\n\nIf you\u2019re facing issues with the above methods or prefer direct assistance:\n\n1. **Contact HR:** Reach out to your company's HR or payroll department.\n2. **Request PF Statement:** Ask them to provide your latest PF statement or guide you on accessing it through company portals.\n3. **Verify Details:** Ensure all your personal and bank details are accurate to avoid discrepancies.\n\n### **6. Check Your Latest Salary Slip**\n\nOften, your PF contributions and current balance are reflected in your monthly salary slip.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Obtain Salary Slip:** Access your latest salary slip provided by your employer.\n2. **Review EPF Section:** Look for the **EPF** or **Provident Fund** section.\n3. **Note the Balance:** Your current PF balance and monthly contributions will be listed there.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for a Smooth PF Balance Check:**\n\n- **Ensure UAN Activation:** If your UAN isn\u2019t activated, log in at the [EPFO Member Portal](https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/) and complete the activation process.\n  \n- **Update KYC Details:** Keep your Aadhaar, PAN, and bank details up-to-date in the EPFO portal to avoid issues.\n\n- **Password Security:** Use a strong password for your EPFO account and change it periodically for security.\n\n- **Regular Checks:** Periodically monitor your PF balance to ensure regular contributions and catch any discrepancies early.\n\nBy following these methods, you can conveniently keep track of your Provident Fund balance and manage your retirement savings effectively.",
